# GUIDE

## 1.0 Quick Setup
### 1.1 Models
Make sure to update each of the below model selections to prevent errors when running the workflow:
- Checkpoints - Each checkpoint selector needs to be updated with a valid checkpoint downloaded on your machine. Please use the selection box to chose one.
    - Use SDXL checkpoint models for CHECKPOINT 1
    - Use SD 1.5 checkpoint models for CHECKPOINT 2
    - You can chose to change this out later, this is just the default settings.
- Upscaler - The UPSCALER module has an Upscaler Model selector that needs to be updated to a model you have already downloaded. If you don't have any downloaded, please use the manager to install an upscaler model.
- Ultralytics Model - This model is loaded in the AfterDetailer module and is used for Face / Hand / Body detection. Please make sure to update the selection to one you have downloaded. Like the upscaler model, you can download one through the manager.
## 2.0 Checkpoint Selection
### 2.1 Define your Checkpoints
- There are 4 separate checkpoint loaders. You **DO NOT** need to use all 4 of them, **DO** need to set a valid checkpoint for each.
- For each, the checkpoint will only be loaded to memory if it is assigned to a module (ie. TXT2IMG, UPSCALER, etc.).
- To assign an checkpoint to a model, drag a line from the output of **CHECKPOINT #** to the input with the module name.

### 2.2 Chosing your Checkpoints
- The TXT2IMG, UPSCALER, and AfterDetailer modules all use SDXL checkpoints.
- The SegmentAnything module uses an SD 1.5 checkpoint.
- Make sure you have the correct type of checkpoint associated with correct module.

### 2.3 Extensions
- Nodes with the label **EXTENSION** are meant to support you adding your own modules to this workflow if you desire.
- If you add an additional module to the workflow, please link it up to an **EXTENSION** node as it will maintain the flow of the workflow.

## 3.0 Modules
### 3.1 What are modules?
- Modules are sections of this workflow where images are generated or modified.
- They are the sections you will be most concerned with when attempting to generate an image.

### 3.2 Module Commonalities
- Each module contains a **POSITIVE** and **NEGATIVE** prompt input.
-  Each module will contain the **SETTINGS** required to make the module function.
    - The settings in the **BLUE** nodes are the ones you will be more likely to update.
    - The settings **NOT** in the **BLUE** nodes should be used with caution and only if you understand the impact as changing them may cause unexpected side-effects.
### 3.3 Module Inputs
- The inputs for each module determine what image the module will be operating on / modifying.
- These inputs can be found above the preview image for the module.
- To define a module input, you will chose which other module output will be the input for the module.
    - Example 1:
        - TXT2IMG -> UPSCALER
        - As the process always starts with a TXT2IMG generation, you will be assigning the output of that generation to the input of the UPSCALER module.
        - The UPSCALER module will use the generated TXT2IMG image and upscale it using an Ultimate SD Upscale process resulting in a new generated image.
    - Example 2:
        - TXT2IMG -> Segment Anything -> After Detailer -> UPSCALER
        - Again, this process starts with a TXT2IMG generation. The output of which will go to the Segment Anything module.
        - The Segment Anything module will auto-generate a mask based on your selection and do an inpainting of the masked area based on your prompt.
        - The output of the Segment Anything module will be sent to After Detailer, where the face (or other specified part) will be auto-detected and inpainted based on your prompt in this module.
        - The output of the After Detailer module will be sent to the UPSCALER module.
        - The UPSCALER module will use the After Detailer image to generate a new upscaled image.
